<subSubSection pageId="261" pageNumber="866" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="261.[166,1372,291,956]" pageId="261" pageNumber="866">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,279,568,602]" pageId="261" pageNumber="866">Habitat.</emphasis>
Highland primary montane forest at elevations of 920-2930 m in Borneo and 700-2400 m in Sumatra.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="261" pageNumber="866" type="food_feeding">
<paragraph blockId="261.[166,1372,291,956]" pageId="261" pageNumber="866">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,434,647,681]" pageId="261" pageNumber="866">Food and Feeding.</emphasis>
Stomach contents included “vegetable matter, apparently shoots, twigs and bark.” One specimen was captured with a crab bait.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
